Name: TopicalCoverageReference
Description: Reference to a previously defined topical coverage.

Name: TopicalCoverage
Description: Description of the topical coverage of the data described in a particular DDI module.

Name: SpatialCoverageReference
Description: Reference to a previously defined spatial coverage.

Name: SpatialCoverage
Description: Description of the geographic coverage of the data described in a particular DDI module.

Name: TemporalCoverageReference
Description: Reference to a previously defined temporal coverage.

Name: TemporalCoverage
Description: Description of the temporal coverage of the data described in a particular DDI module.

Name: RestrictionProcess
Description: Allows for a specific machine actionable description of the restriction process using a GenerationInstructionReference, if one currently exists, or through a CommandCode. In the case of a physical instance, the RestrictionProcess would be the same as a case, record or variable selection process.

Name: IsRestrictionOfParentCoverage
Description: If the coverage described within this object is a restriction of the coverage of its parent study or group set this attribute to "true". If the coverage of a specific type (spatial, topical, or temporal) is not a restriction, include this coverage type by reference to that described in parent. Create a new coverage for the type being restricted.
